}} requires attacks in at least 75 % 75\\% of each active voice’s bars. The diagnostics are nested: A dist ⇒ A θ ⇒ A tr ⇒ A leg . A_{\\mathrm{dist}}\\Rightarrow A_{\\theta}\\Rightarrow A_{\\mathrm{tr}}\\Rightarrow A_{\\mathrm{leg}}. (11) These tiers reuse process records and are diagnostics, not release decisions. After score assembly, the separately implemented constraint audit A audit A_{\\mathrm{audit}} (Appendix B ) rescans the retained candidate. The output contract is Compose ​ ( x ) = { S ⋆ , A audit ​ ( S ⋆ ) = 1 , Failure , otherwise . \\textsc{Compose}(x)=\\begin{cases}S^{\\star},&A_{\\mathrm{audit}}(S^{\\star})=1,\\\\ \\textsc{Failure},&\\text{otherwise}.\\end{cases} The gate does not trigger further generation; failed candidates remain stored only for analysis. Stored-blueprint agreement is reported separately because operative replans are not fully materialised. Figure 2: Per-model cross-voice collision rates for raw and harness candidates, normalised by overlapping cross-voice event pairs (overlap > 10 − 3 >10^{-3} beats). Dashed hollow lines denote raw candidates and solid filled lines denote harness candidates. Points show three-run means after pooling retained overlap pairs within each setting; error bars show one standard deviation. Raw rates are conditional on parseability. One-voice rates are zero by convention because no cross-voice pair exists. 4 Experimental Design Tasks. We use 40 40 single-factor tasks: a 20 20 -task length sweep ( 8 8 – 64 64 bars, two voices) and a 20 20 -task texture sweep ( 1 1 – 4 4 voices, eight bars), sharing a two-voice/eight-bar anchor. Each task contains one mild writing concern. Full briefs and inventories appear in Appendix C . Models. DeepSeek V4 Pro/Flash, GPT-5 Nano, and Qwen3 235B-A22B (Qwen3 235B) run both raw and in-harness. The full model inventory appears in Appendix C . Expert evaluation. Five experts compare 24 24 anonymised Qwen3 235B pairs ( 8 8 tasks × \\times three contrasts). Experimental setup. The four paired models share one API and decoding configuration (Appendix D ). A task’s prime row is fixed across models, conditions, and runs; seeds control only LLM sampling. After averaging runs within task, we report point estimates and 2000 2000 -resample nonparametric family-clustered bootstrap (Efron 1979 ) confidence intervals (CIs). Each draw samples the ten prompt families with their four tasks. The ablation study comprises the deterministic backbone, raw generation, Self-Refine, Soft rules, and the full ha", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false, "persistedOutputPath": "/inspire/qb-ilm/project/video-generation/chenxie-25019/hyr/iHateTheWorld555.github.io/.claude-review/projects/-inspire-qb-ilm-project-video-generation-chenxie-25019-hyr-iHateTheWorld555-github-io/22975452-35dc-4324-bcac-9d0529b887d6/tool-results/b5qejf1j0.txt", "persistedOutputSize": 81464}}
