le retaining all four tasks in a sampled family. These remain descriptive fixed-bank sensitivity summaries rather than population-level significance tests. Deterministic-backbone ablations ( 480 480 offline runs: 40 40 tasks × 4 \\times\\,4 conditions × 3 \\times\\,3 seeds, no LLM). Table 14 adds CIs to the top block of Table 1 . LLM-in-the-loop ablations ( 360 360 Qwen3 235B runs: 40 40 tasks × 3 \\times\\,3 conditions × 3 \\times\\,3 seeds). Table 15 adds CIs and the theme delta to the middle block of Table 1 . Table 14: Deterministic-backbone ablations with descriptive family-clustered bootstrap 95 % 95\\% intervals (vs. full harness). Condition Δ \\Delta accepted Δ \\Delta ind. core Δ \\Delta degeneracy No repair − 0.192 ​ [ − 0.267 , − 0.117 ] -0.192\\ [-0.267,-0.117] + 0.050 ​ [ 0.000 , 0.100 ] +0.050\\ [0.000,0.100] − 0.006 ​ [ − 0.008 , − 0.003 ] -0.006\\ [-0.008,-0.003] No repair + no replan − 0.192 ​ [ − 0.267 , − 0.117 ] -0.192\\ [-0.267,-0.117] + 0.025 ​ [ − 0.017 , 0.067 ] +0.025\\ [-0.017,0.067] − 0.004 ​ [ − 0.007 , − 0.002 ] -0.004\\ [-0.007,-0.002] No replan − 0.025 ​ [ − 0.050 , 0.000 ] -0.025\\ [-0.050,0.000] + 0.025 ​ [ − 0.017 , 0.067 ] +0.025\\ [-0.017,0.067] + 0.001 ​ [ 0.000 , 0.001 ] +0.001\\ [0.000,0.001] The no-repair condition averages 11.17 11.17 fewer events ( 95 % 95\\% CI [ − 13.53 , − 9.03 ] [-13.53,-9.03] ) and 0.713 0.713 fewer notes per bar ( [ − 0.921 , − 0.517 ] [-0.921,-0.517] ) than the full harness, while mean active-bar coverage changes by only − 0.001 -0.001 ( [ − 0.002 , 0.000 ] [-0.002,0.000] ) and voice realisation does not change. Because the narrow check conditions on generated overlap opportunities, the sparser candidate may provide fewer chances to collide. The observed + 0.050 +0.050 delta therefore cannot establish that removing repair improves candidate consistency; the offline records retain neither pairwise overlap counts nor sufficient artefacts to recompute the broader audit for this ablation. Table 15: LLM-in